
[1]pungent

   PUN'GENT, a. [L. pungens,pungo.] Pricking; stimulating; as pungent
   snuff.

   The pungent grains of titillating dust.

   1. Acrid; affecting the tongue like small sharp points; as the sharp
   and pungent taste of acids.

   2. Piercing; sharp; as pungent pains; pungent grief.

   3. Acrimonious; biting.
